to note:wrt (5)
1.create python and flask env in idle
pip install "Flask==2.2.2"

2.create server.py file and code main structure as follows:
# Import the Flask class from the flask module
from flask import Flask

# Create an instance of the Flask class, passing in the name of the current module
app = Flask(__name__)

# Define a route for the root URL ("/")
@app.route("/")
def hello_world():
    # Function that handles requests to the root URL
    return "Hello, World!"

3.returning json--Use the jsonify() method on a string
# Import the Flask class from the flask module
from flask import Flask

# Create an instance of the Flask class, passing in the name of the current module
app = Flask(__name__)

# Define a route for the root URL ("/")
@app.route("/")
def home():
    # Function that handles requests to the root URL
    # Create a dictionary to return as a response
    return {"message": "Learning Flask"}
